  "text": "The mechanisms that heat up or temper antagonistic interactions are not clear; there remains a need to gain a fuller view of the coevolutionary dynamics that are driven by tolerance evolution and the new adaptive peaks this presents to parasites. Most tolerance theory omits successive host [CITATION_1] or parasite [CITATION_2] counteradaptation, and changes in variance that may accompany alterations in the host fitness-parasite fitness relationship have been little studied in fully coevolutionary models. Further modeling can only benefit from empirical parameterization of parasitism under real-world levels of genetic and environmental variation.",
